ant]] (d. 1744) *[[1697]] &ndash; [[Johann Gottlieb Görner]], German organist and composer (d. 1778) *[[1728]] &ndash; [[Joseph Black]], French-Scottish physician and chemist (d. 1799) *[[1730]] &ndash; [[Henry Clinton (British Army officer, born 1730)|Henry Clinton]], English general and politician (d. 1795) *[[1755]] &ndash; [[Louise Élisabeth Vigée Le Brun]], French painter (d. 1842) *[[1786]] &ndash; [[John Franklin]], English admiral and politician, 4th [[Governor of Tasmania|Lieutenant Governor of Van Diemen's Land]] (d. 1847) *[[1800]] &ndash; [[George Bingham, 3rd Earl of Lucan]], English field marshal and politician (d. 1888) *[[1808]] &ndash; [[Caleb Blood Smith]], American journalist, lawyer, and politician, 6th [[United States Secretary of the Interior]] (d. 1864) *[[1821]] &ndash; [[Ford Madox Brown]], French-English soldier and painter (d. 1893) *[[1823]] &ndash; [[Gotthold Eisenstein]], German mathematician and academic (d. 1852) *[[1826]] &ndash; [[Sir James Corry, 1st Baronet]], British politician (d. 1891) *[[1827]] &ndash; [[Octave Crémazie]], Canadian poet and bookseller (d. 1879) *[[1839]] &ndash; [[Antonio Starabba, Marchese di Rudinì]], Italian politician, 12th [[Prime Minister of Italy]] (d. 1908) *[[1834]] &ndash; [[Charles Lennox Richardson]], English merchant (d. 1862) *[[1844]] &ndash; [[Anatole France]], French journalist, novelist, and poet, [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 1924) *[[1847]] &ndash; [[Hans Auer]], Swiss-Austrian architect, designed the [[Federal Palace of Switzerland]] (d. 1906) *[[1848]] &ndash; [[Kandukuri Veeresalingam]], Indian author and activist (d. 1919) *[[1851]] &ndash; [[Ponnambalam Ramanathan]], Sri Lankan lawyer and politician, 3rd [[Solicitor General of Sri Lanka]] (d. 1930) *[[1864]] &ndash; [[Rose Talbot Bullard]], American medical doctor and professor (d. 1915) *[[1865]] &ndash; [[Harry Chauvel]], Australian general (d. 1945) *[[1866]] &ndash; [[José de Diego]], Puerto Rican journalis